  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p>The <strong>Electrical Engineer</strong> – Construction Related Works is responsible for supervising, coordinating, and executing all electrical construction activities on site. The role ensures that electrical works are carried out in accordance with approved drawings, technical specifications, safety standards, and project schedules, while maintaining quality and compliance with applicable codes and regulations.<br /></p><ul><li><p>Supervise and coordinate electrical construction works including power distribution, lighting, earthing, and low-current systems.</p></li><li><p>Review electrical drawings, shop drawings, material submittals, and method statements.</p></li><li><p>Ensure electrical installations comply with project specifications, approved drawings, and applicable standards.</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with civil, mechanical, and other engineering teams to avoid conflicts and delays.</p></li><li><p>Monitor site progress and prepare daily and weekly reports.</p></li><li><p>Inspect materials delivered to site and ensure compliance with approved submittals.</p></li><li><p>Conduct site inspections, testing, commissioning, and snag-list clearance.</p></li><li><p>Ensure strict compliance with health, safety, and environmental (HSE) requirements.</p></li><li><p>Identify and resolve technical issues during construction.</p></li><li><p>Support project handover, as-built drawings, and documentation.<br /><br /><strong>Experience</strong></p><ul><li><p>3–7 years of experience in electrical construction works.</p></li><li><p>Proven experience in site supervision for building, industrial, or infrastructure projects.</p></li></ul></li></ul>",
